          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Democrats, Rahm con=
tinued, need to put aside purity tests and find candidates who aren=E2=80=
=99t afraid to piss off the language police and progressive scolds that see=
m to spook so many operatives in the party. Emanuel sounded exasperated whe=
n he recalled how progressives savaged Biden after he used the term =E2=80=
=9Cillegal alien=E2=80=9D in his State of the Union address earlier this ye=
ar, a comment he was forced to apologize for. =E2=80=9CYou are illegally co=
ming across the border, and you are an immigrant,=E2=80=9D said Emanuel. =
=E2=80=9CI mean, come on.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Emanuel said that Democrats nee=
d to remind voters that they are the party of the little guy, standing up t=
o big banks and billionaires. He also put a blunter edge on a sentiment I=
=E2=80=99d heard a lot from pragmatic strategists in recent years: That Dem=
ocrats can only win when they start<i> punching left</i> and pushing
back against the orthodoxies that have spread from elite campuses into part=
y committees and big-city newsrooms. Grad school concepts about identity, g=
ender, race, or crime that are either unpopular, inscrutable, or far remove=
d from people=E2=80=99s daily lives.<br/><br/>That=E2=80=99s one reason cer=
tain Senate candidates, including members of the =E2=80=9906 class such as =
<b>Jon</b> <b>Tester</b> and <b>Sherrod</b> <b>Brown</b>, outran Harris in =
red states, he said. And it explains why winning candidates <b>Tammy</b> <b=
>Baldwin</b>, <b>Ruben</b> <b>Gallego</b>, and <b>Jacky</b> <b>Rosen</b> ha=
ve white-knuckled their way to victory. They didn=E2=80=99t let their races=
 get nationalized, and they worked overtime to talk less about Trump and th=
e culture wars, and more about the kitchen table. =E2=80=9CWe don=E2=80=99t=
 understand that working-class people are more than just the summation of t=
heir wallet,=E2=80=9D Emanuel said. =E2=80=9CThey have kids that go to scho=
ol. They care about public safety. Like, we are telling people
crime is going down, but they go to CVS and everything is locked up and no =
one is working there? That doesn=E2=80=99t compute, I=E2=80=99m sorry. Save=
 your academic presentations for the Aspen Ideas Festival.=E2=80=9D<br/><br=
/>Punching left, of course, is more easily said than done, as Congressman <=
b>Seth Moulton</b> learned over the weekend when he spoke to <i>The</i> <i>=
New York Times </i>with unusual honesty about trans athletes playing in wom=
en=E2=80=99s and girls sports. =E2=80=9CI have two little girls, I don=E2=
=80=99t want them getting run over on a playing field by a male or formerly=
 male athlete, but as a Democrat I=E2=80=99m supposed to be afraid to say t=
hat.=E2=80=9D One of Moulton=E2=80=99s staffers resigned in protest, and he=
 was condemned by the head of the Massachusetts Democratic Party. At the sa=
me time, in polls, large majorities of the country agree with Moulton=E2=80=
=99s take.<br/><br/>There=E2=80=99s no simple blueprint here. The only cons=
ensus I=E2=80=99ve been able to pick up on from Democrats, however vague, i=
s that the
party needs to get back to listening to voters rather than talking at them.=
 Congresswoman <b>Marie Gluesenkamp Perez</b>, a flannel-wearing Democrat w=
ho won reelection last week in a southwestern Washington district that also=
 voted for Trump, has been doing the media rounds the last few days explain=
ing how she pulled out her race while other Democrats stumbled in what was =
a terrible political environment. But when I talked to her Monday, even she=
 acknowledged there were limits to how much national Democrats could learn =
from her win. =E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99t want to be a poster child or a cardb=
oard cutout,=E2=80=9D Gluesenkamp Perez told me. =E2=80=9CIf there is a mod=
el here, it=E2=80=99s just that you have to fight for where you come from, =
to show up and do the work. That has to be the motivator, and it=E2=80=99s =
how you break the ideological map.=E2=80=9D<br/></td>
